experience.description:
I was part of the Rio 2016 Olympic Committee Results team.
This team's scope of work was enormous. We had diverse competencies. But basically, we were responsible for a central system, where the competition results were entered, processed and stored. This system provided this data to several other systems such as scoreboards, web applications, mobile applications, results totems, in addition to providing the same information to the main broadcasters in the world.
We divided it up by sport, so each Olympic sport had a team consisting of a Facility Results Manager, a Facility Results Assistant and in some cases, a tester. In the Rio2016 edition of the Olympic Games, a mobile application was made available for the first time, where it was possible to follow the results of the competition in real time and from anywhere.

- Quality Assurance – Software and Service;
- Collecting test, Dissemination and Quality of competition results information;
- Data validation and quality of the competition results and the dissemination of it to different media (intranet, internet, scoreboard, mobile, TV, etc.);
- Test Case Development;
- Responsible for the testing schedule planning;
- Implementation, Validation / Report of Tests and Results;
- Responsible for planning the results of cell installations in the test and Olympic events;
- Infrastructure and Workforce needs planning;
- Volunteers management at official event – 60 volunteers at the Olympic period and 30 in the Paralympic;
- Test Event Planning - With needs and volunteer management, local distribution demand and consumption of materials – 30 Volunteers;
- Volunteer in other sports Test Events helping with Venue Management, leading other Volunteers and solving needs - Taekwondo

Automation Engineer responsible for automation projects in mobile devices (android). I Serve as a technical reference and support to the team in their projects (web and mobile).
Setting up and maintaining the mobile testing framework from scratch using Kotlin and Google Espresso across the multiple projects. 
Create an E2E acceptance testing framework from scratch using Kotlin, Appium and Cucumber (Behaviour Driven Development).
Mentoring and supporting other scrum teams creating E2E test automation frameworks using Java and Selenium such as web products when needed. 

Key Accomplishments:
- Achieved a large number of automated scenarios in a short period of time, thereby increasing test coverage and the quality of applications as a whole;
- Best scenarios and documentation, that influenced on the product overall quality and less bugs in production;
- Leaded the agile methods implementation on the company (Scrum and Kanban); increased the number of releases per month and quality of them;
- Leaded the automation effort implementation; improved the products quality, reduced the costs and time to conduct the tests and secured a pay rise.
